<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900525-0027</DOCNO><DOCID>900525-0027.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Chrysler Corp.:   Canadian Unit Will Spend   $253.2 Million on Facility</HL><DATE>05/25/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2</SO><CO>   C</CO><IN>AUTOMOBILES (AUT)</IN><LP>   Chrysler Canada Ltd., said it plans to spend 300 millionCanadian dollars ($253.2 million) at its Windsor, Ontario,minivan plant.   The Toronto-based company said C$21 million will be spentin plant improvements at the facility, with the remainingC$280 million to be spent on product development. The plantwill build the redesigned 1991 minivan.</LP><TEXT>   The Canadian unit of Chrysler Corp. also said its PilletteRoad assembly plant in Windsor has &quot;a good future.&quot; There hadbeen some talk of the plant's being shut down. The plant isChrysler's only source of large, rear-wheel-drive commercialvans and wagons.   Chrylser Canada said it will invest more than C$100million in new equipment and plant improvements at thePillette plant over the next three years.</TEXT></DOC>